{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require new minimum wages be paid from 1 April irrespective of pay period",
        "additional_details": "Companies are able to pay staff for less than the minimum wage if the relevant pay period started before 1 April. This means that workers can lose out on significant pay increases. We believe that this unacceptable.",
        "background": "We want the Government to amend rules that allow old minimum wages to be paid after 1 April if the relevant pay period started before 1 April, so that the minimum wage has to be paid from 1 April, irrespective of when the pay period began.",
        "closed_at": null,
